      <h1 id="u79846-2">QUICK INFO</h1>
     </div>
     <!-- /m_editable -->
     <!-- m_editable region-id="editable-static-tag-U79845-BP_infinity" template="montréal.html" data-type="html" data-ice-options="disableImageResize,link,txtStyleTarget" -->
     <div class="text-body-padding-top-5px ASM---p---body-text clearfix colelem shared_content" id="u79845-20" data-muse-uid="U79845" data-muse-type="txt_frame" data-IBE-flags="txtStyleSrc" data-content-guid="u79845-20_content"><!-- content -->
      <p id="u79845-2">1. The unit of currency is the Canadian dollar, with coins in denominations of 5, 10 and 25 cents, and $1 (a large gold-coloured coin) and $2 (a large bimetallic coin). Bills in $5 (blue), $10 (purple) and $20 (green) are in common circulation and you can get $50s (red) and $100s (brown) from banks, thought not from most automatic teller machines (ATMs).</p>
      <p id="u79845-3">&nbsp;</p>
      <p id="u79845-5">The Canadian Dollar currently exchanges at approximately $1.00 CAN to $0.80 US cents.</p>
      <p id="u79845-6">&nbsp;</p>
      <p id="u79845-8">2. The average temperatures in July will vary from 18° - 27°C (65 - 80°F). Keep this in mind when packing.</p>
      <p id="u79845-9">&nbsp;</p>
      <p id="u79845-11">3. Electrical Current in Montréal is AC 110 Volts, 60 cycles</p>
      <p id="u79845-12">&nbsp;</p>
      <p id="u79845-14">4. A list of dress codes has been suggested for each of the events. Please have a look at the programme itinerary as a guideline of the activities and events in which you will be participating.</p>
      <p id="u79845-15">&nbsp;</p>
      <p id="u79845-17">As always, dress comfortably for travelling.&nbsp; Make sure you have the necessities, a change of clothes, reading material, prescription medications etc., in your carry-on bag.&nbsp; Do not pack any liquids that do not comply with the 3-1-1 regulations, or sharp objects, penknives, scissors, (nail clippers are okay nowadays) etc., in your carry-on bag. They may be taken from you.</p>
      <p id="u79845-18">&nbsp;</p>
